---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Container from '../components/ui/Container.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Submit a Post" description="How to submit a post to the NSIETeam Blog.">
  <section class="pt-24 pb-16 md:pt-32 md:pb-20">
    <Container>
      <div class="max-w-readable">
        <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl tracking-tight text-[#212529] mb-8">
          Submit a Post
        </h1>

        <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none text-[#212529] space-y-6 leading-relaxed">
          <p class="text-lg">
            We welcome contributions from team members and collaborators. The
            submission process uses GitHub Issues to keep things transparent and
            trackable.
          </p>

          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-[#212529] mt-10 mb-4">Submission Workflow</h2>

          <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-4 text-[#212529]">
            <li>
              <strong>Go to the GitHub repository</strong> &mdash; Navigate to the
              NSIETeam Blog repository on GitHub.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Open a new Issue using the "Blog Post" template</strong> &mdash;
              Select the "Blog Post" issue template to get started with the correct
              format.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Fill in the required fields</strong> &mdash; Provide the post
              title, a short description, relevant tags, and the topic category
              (Research, Engineering, Notes, or News).
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Write the content in Markdown</strong> &mdash; Compose the
              body of your post using standard Markdown syntax. You may include
              code blocks, headings, lists, and links.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Submit the issue for review</strong> &mdash; Once submitted,
              the editorial team will review your post for clarity, accuracy, and
              alignment with the blog's standards.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Publication</strong> &mdash; After approval, your post will
              be published as a blog post on the NSIETeam Blog.
            </li>
          </ol>

          <div class="mt-10">
            <a
              href="https://github.com/nsieteam/nsieteam-blog/issues/new"
              class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-[#b31b1b] text-white font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-[#8b0000] transition-colors duration-200"
            >
              Open GitHub Issue
            </a>
          </div>

          <p class="mt-8 text-[#6c757d] text-sm">
            If you have questions about the submission process, please reach out
            to the editorial team through the repository discussions or internal
            channels.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
